    public interface PsiTypeCodeFragment

        PsiType getType()
         throws PsiTypeCodeFragment.TypeSyntaxException,

        Returns the type referenced by the code fragment.
        Returns:
        the referenced type.
        Throws:
        PsiTypeCodeFragment.TypeSyntaxException - if the code fragment contains a syntax error.
        PsiTypeCodeFragment.NoTypeException - if the contents of the code fragment is not a Java type.

      • isVoidValid

        boolean isVoidValid()
        Checks if void is treated as a valid type for the contents of the code fragment.
        Returns:
        true if void is a valid type, false otherwise.
